[2026-03-26] ## ✅ Fixed!

The error is now resolved. The problem was that `split-screen-sync.js` loads with the `defer` attribute, which means it executes after the DOM is parsed. But the inline `onclick` handlers were trying to call functions that didn't exist yet.

**What I fixed:**
- ✅ Removed all inline `onclick` handlers
- ✅ Added proper event listeners in `DOMContentLoaded`
- ✅ Used event delegation for dynamic elements (day edit buttons)
- ✅ Fixed the AI suggestion buttons
- ✅ Fixed preview modal butt

